  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promotion of Peaceful Transhumance in the Liptako-Gourma Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to support key actors in the three Liptako-Gourma countries of Burkina Faso, Mali and Niger, to prevent and effectively manage conflicts related to transhumance in the border areas. First, it aims to strengthen the capacities of information collection and analysis linked to transhumance movements to create an early warning system to avoid potential conflict. Secondly, it equips actors to better prevent and manage conflicts through appropriate mechanisms and procedures. Lastly, it implements actions to strengthen the resilience of stakeholders.</narrative>
  </description>
